D45.formula:
=_xlfn.LET(
_xlpm.movAndTier, $D$4+$D$10,
_xlpm.movBase,  6+$D$10,
_xlpm.movStart,IF(_xlpm.movAndTier>_xlpm.movBase,_xlpm.movAndTier,_xlpm.movBase),
_xlpm.CutAbove, IF($D$23="Cut Above",_xlfn.IFS($D$4<5,1,$D$4<8,2,D4>7,3),0),

_xlpm.mType, _xlfn.IFS(
AND($D$22="Swift",$D$4<5),2,
AND($D$22="Swift",$D$4<7),3,
AND($D$22="Swift",$D$4<9),4,
AND($D$22="Swift",$D$4<11),5,
$D$22="Vanguard", $D$12,
$D$22="Alternative Locomotion: Swinging",1,
$D$22="Alternative Locomotion: Super Jump",1,
$D$22="Alternative Locomotion: Teleportation",-2,
$D$22<>"Swift",0),

_xlpm.movTotal, _xlpm.movStart+_xlpm.mType+_xlpm.CutAbove,
_xlpm.movTotal
)

labels.H9: Adds to Resolve, Initiative, Accuracy score
labels.H10: Adds to Movement Speed, Initiative, Avoidance score
labels.H11: Adds to Stability, Capacity, Damage score
labels.H12: Adds to Vitality and Durability score
labels.H15: Your character's ability to notice things in the world.
labels.H55: You can make a base attack.
labels.H56: Increase your Avoidance by your Tier until the start of your next turn.
labels.H57: Increase your DR by your Tier until the start of your next turn.
labels.H58: Increase all types of Resistance by your Tier until the start of your next turn.
labels.H59: Increase your next attacks Accuracy roll by your Tier until the end of your next turn.
labels.H60: Increase your Damage by your Tier until the end of your next turn.
labels.H61: Increase your Condition roll by your Tier until the end of your next turn.
labels.H62: You take the Aim, Empower, or Refine Actions but targeting an adjacent ally instead.
labels.H63: Pick up and move a willing character with you. You move at half speed while moving them.
labels.H64: Pick an adjacent character or object. The next non-direct attack made against them automatically hits you instead.
labels.H65: Interact with a thing in the environment that takes most of your attention such as a car, computer, or heavy object. Picking up small items or simple tasks such as pressing a button only consumes a Quick Action.
labels.H66: You can move your full Movement Speed again.
labels.H67: While outside of the Direct Perception of a character you can attempt to conceal your presence from them with a Stealth check vs their Perception. Once hidden, they remember your last known location and may investigate or attack that area. You remain hidden until you take a noticeable action such as attacking or entering their Direct Perception again. On your turn you may attempt to move from cover to cover, making another check. Depending on the distance, your GM may grant your roll a penalty.
labels.H68: You delay your action until a specified point chosen when you take this action. GM determines if the specified scenario is specific enough.

vl_table.Alternative Locomotion: Flight: You can move your full movement in any direction.
vl_table.Alternative Locomotion: Teleportation: You can instantly move your movement speed to any location you can see. -2 to your Movement Speed up to Tier 6 and -3 from Tier 7 to 10.
vl_table.Alternative Locomotion: Portal: You can create a portal between 2 points
vl_table.Alternative Locomotion: Swinging: You can move through the air if you have a point to grapple onto. Increase your movement speed by 1 space up to Tier 6 and by 2 for 7 and higher.
vl_table.Alternative Locomotion: Super Jump: You can jump an amount equal to your full movement. Increase your movement speed by 1 space up to Tier 6 and by 2 for 7 and higher.
vl_table.Swift: Increase your movement speed by half your Tier (round up).
vl_table.Skirmisher: You don’t provoke attacks of opportunity.
vl_table.Parkour Runner: You are unaffected by difficult terrain; you can swim or move through difficult terrain at normal speed. You can walk on water and stick to all surfaces.
vl_table.Behemoth: You can’t be slowed or knocked prone. Additionally, you are immune to the dazed condition.
vl_table.Bulwark: Your reach is increased by 1 space. Additionally, you may make an opportunity attack when an enemy attempts to enter your reach.
vl_table.Mole: You can burrow through most materials and barriers. You move through rock and anything softer at your normal speed. For anything harder, you move through at half speed or slower at GM discretion. When selecting this archetype, determine whether you leave a tunnel behind when you burrow. If you do not, you may not end your turn underground.
vl_table.Vanguard: Add your Endurance to your movement speed.  Get to your allies and enemies faster while being able to absorb hits.
vl_table.AOE Specialist: You gain the AOE Attack Type for 0p.
vl_table.Direct Specialist: You gain the Direct Attack Type for 0p.
vl_table.Single Target: You gain both Melee and Ranged Attack Types for 0p.
vl_table.Damage: Your primary effect type is damage. Also, you can still access Basic Conditions as separate attacks.
vl_table.Hybrid: You gain the Hybrid for 0p. All attacks must be Hybrid.
vl_table.Crowd Control / De-buffer: You gain all Advanced condition effects, for 0p. Subtract your Tier from your Damage rolls.
vl_table.Versatile Master: You have 2 Quick Actions. Making a Primary Action a Quick Action only cost 10 points.
vl_table.Cut Above: Increase the following stats by 1: Accuracy, Damage, Conditions, Avoidance, Durability, Resistances, Initiative, Movement. If you are Tier 5-7, instead increase by 2, if you are Tier 8+, increase by 3.
vl_table.Extraordinary: You gain an additional (Tier -2) x 15 in points for your main pool of points. You cannot use these points to purchase Traits or Flaws.
vl_table.Specialized: You may pick 1 core stat with which to be proficient, checks involving that core stat always add your Tier bonus twice to rolls. You can’t purchase Expertise. You get less points in your Utility point pool.
vl_table.Jack of All Trades: Add your Tier bonus once to all Skill Checks. You cannot purchase Expertise. You get less points in your Utility point pool.
vl_table.Practical: Purchase Expertise, Features, Senses, Descriptors normally.
vl_table.Straightforward: Focuses on creating powerful attacks at the cost of versatility. You can only use 1 specific Limit chosen when you take this archetype, that limit must be on all attacks. That limit returns its normal Points x (Tier/2).
vl_table.Paragon: Straightforward and simple, with reliable attacks of consistent power. No trade-offs, ideal for balanced gameplay.Each special attack gets 10 × Tier points to distribute. You cannot take any limits.
vl_table.One Trick: Best for building a single, incredibly powerful ability that fits a high-risk, high-reward playstyle. You only have a single special attack. You have Tier × 20 points to create this ability.
vl_table.Specialist: Focuses on creating powerful attacks at the cost of meeting multiple conditions for each of your attacks. You can only use 3 specific Limits chosen when you take this archetype, those limits must be on each attack each return their normal Points x (Tier/3).
vl_table.Shared Uses: Flexible and encourages tactical planning. Perfect for spellcaster-style builds with strong resource management needs. You cannot take any limits. You have 10 shared uses. Each special attack uses between 1-3 mana, chosen when building, and gives a discount of Tier × 10 points upon use.
vl_table.Normal: Special Attacks: Maximum flexibility for creating unique or specialized abilities.   You get 3 Specialty Upgrades. All limits return Points x (Tier / 6)
vl_table.Dual-Natured: For those seeking a balance between Raw Power and Versatility. You have 2 Special Attack, each gets 15 x Tier points to procure upgrades. You cannot take any limits.
vl_table.Basic: For those seeking a more simple but powerful style of gameplay. You can add up to 10 x Tier points of upgrades on your base attack.  You cannot take any limits.
